## Appendix D Scalability of the VaR Framework

We define the \(\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}\) q-value function (Q-function) for any policy \(\pi\in\Pi_{D}\) as \(\bm{q}^{\pi}:S\times A\to\mathbb{R}\) such that for any state \(s\) and action \(a\), \(\bm{q}^{\pi}(s,a)=\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}[\bm{p}_{s,a}^{\mathsf{T}}(\bm{r}_{s,a}+ \gamma\bm{v}^{\pi})]\), where \(\bm{v}^{\pi}=\mathcal{T}_{\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}}^{\mathsf{T}}\bm{v}^{\pi}\) is the fixed point of the \(\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}\) Bellman evaluation operator for policy \(\pi\). We will use \(\hat{\bm{q}}\) to denote the q-value function corresponding to the optimal \(\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}\) policy \(\hat{\pi}\), i.e., \(\hat{\pi}(s)=\arg\max_{a\in A}\hat{\bm{q}}(s,a)\).

Let \(\hat{\bm{q}}_{\bm{\theta}}\) and \(\hat{\bm{q}}_{\tilde{\bm{\theta}}}\) denote the parameterized Q-value and corresponding target Q-value networks with parameters \(\hat{\bm{\theta}}\in\Theta\) and \(\bar{\bm{\theta}}\in\Theta\) respectively. Here \(\hat{\bm{q}}_{\bm{\theta}}\) and \(\hat{\bm{q}}_{\tilde{\bm{\theta}}}\) may represent any function approximators with parameter space \(\Theta\).

The optimal Q-value network (\(\hat{q}_{\bm{\theta}^{*}}\)) can be learned by simply minimizing the empirical \(\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}\) Bellman residual error \(J_{\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}}(\bm{\theta})\), i.e.,

\[\begin{split}\hat{q}_{\bm{\theta}^{*}}&=\operatorname*{ arg\,min}_{\theta\in\Theta}J_{\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}}(\bm{\theta})\\ &=\operatorname*{arg\,min}_{\bm{\theta}\in\Theta}\mathbb{E}_{(s,a )\sim\mathcal{D}}\left[\left(q_{\bm{\theta}}(s,a)-\max_{\alpha^{\prime}\in \mathcal{A}}\widehat{\mathrm{VaR}_{\alpha}}[\mathbb{E}_{s^{\prime}\sim\tilde{ \bm{p}}_{s,a}}\left[\bm{r}_{s,a}+\gamma\bar{\bm{q}}_{\bm{\theta}}(s^{\prime}, a^{\prime})\right]\right)^{2}\right]\end{split}\] (42)

where data \(\mathcal{D}\) is a list state-action (s, a) tuples that is collected using the current policy on the mean model \(\tilde{\bm{P}}\). In this case, the target Q-value network parameters \(\bar{\bm{\theta}}\) is periodically updated by overwriting the target q-value network parameter with the Q-value network parameters \((\bm{\theta})\).

